ions, -3.98\%; 95\% CI, -14.69\% to 6.72\%; and pre-2014 Medicaid expansions, 1.02\%; 95\% CI, -5.25\% to 7.28\%).{$<$}/p{$><$}h3{$>$}Conclusions and Relevance{$<$}/h3{$><$}p{$>$}Medicaid expansion appears to be associated with meaningful reductions in opioid-related hospital use, possibly attributable to improved care for opioid use disorder in other settings.{$<$}/p{$>$}},
